            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-04-13 00:28:00" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:ἄκανθα&lt;SDBG:ἄκανθα:000000&gt;} ‘thorn plant,’ {D:3.17}) pertaining to being made or consisting of thorns; in the NT, only in the phrase ἀκάνθινον στέφανον, a crown made from a plant with sharp projections on its stem and/or branches; symbol of hardship</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>crown of thorns</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It may be necessary to indicate that this crown of thorns is one made of ‘branches of a thorny bush,’ for the crown did not consist merely of thorns but of thorny vines or branches.</Comments>
